===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}}: a nose — original form of {{och-l|鼻|nose}}. Later phonetically borrowed as an instance of {{liushu|j|nocap=y}} for {{och-l|自|oneself; from}}.

Folk etymology considers the meaning to arise from a habit of pointing at one’s nose to indicate oneself.

